| Property                                             | Category                           | What it tells                                                        | Quick example                                                                           |
| ---------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `display`                                            | **Parent-facing**                  | How **your parent** treats your box (inline, block, flex item, etc.) | `display:inline-block` makes you an inline-level box with your own block layout inside. |
| `vertical-align`                                     | **Parent-facing** (inline context) | How **your box** aligns in the **parent line box**                   | `vertical-align: middle` centers the **box** vs. neighbors; doesn’t center text inside. |
| `position` (`static/relative/absolute/fixed/sticky`) | **Parent-facing**                  | How you participate in normal flow/stacking                          | `position:absolute` removes you from flow; parent/ancestor positions you.               |
| `float` / `clear`                                    | **Parent-facing**                  | How you float alongside siblings                                     | Floats change how siblings wrap around you.                                             |
| `order` (flex/grid)                                  | **Parent-facing**                  | Your position among siblings in parent’s layout                      | Reorders items without changing the DOM.                                                |
| `align-self` (flex/grid)                             | **Parent-facing**                  | How **you** align within your parent’s cross-axis                    | Override parent’s `align-items` for one child.                                          |

